# Google Cloud CLI (gcloud) Usage Guide

## Triggers
**APPLY WHEN:** User needs to investigate GCP resources, query Cloud Logging, manage Cloud Storage, inspect Compute instances, or debug GCP services
**SKIP WHEN:** Using GCP Console or GCP client libraries programmatically

## Core Directive
**Use gcloud for GCP operations** - Query logs, inspect resources, manage services, and debug GCP infrastructure from the command line.

## Installation

```bash
# macOS
brew install --cask google-cloud-sdk

# Linux (official script)
curl https://sdk.cloud.google.com | bash
exec -l $SHELL

# Verify installation
gcloud --version

# Initialize
gcloud init
```

## Configuration

**Set default project:**
```bash
gcloud config set project PROJECT_ID
gcloud config set compute/zone ZONE
gcloud config set compute/region REGION
```

**List configuration:**
```bash
gcloud config list
gcloud config list --format="table(core.project,compute.zone)"
```

**Authenticate:**
```bash
gcloud auth login
gcloud auth application-default login  # For SDK/API access
gcloud auth list
```

## Common Operations

### Compute Engine (VMs)

**List instances:**
```bash
gcloud compute instances list
gcloud compute instances list --filter="status=RUNNING"
gcloud compute instances list --format="table(name,zone,status,networkInterfaces[0].accessConfigs[0].natIP)"
```

**Get instance details:**
```bash
gcloud compute instances describe INSTANCE_NAME --zone ZONE
```

**SSH into instance:**
```bash
gcloud compute ssh INSTANCE_NAME --zone ZONE
```

**Start/stop instances:**
```bash
gcloud compute instances start INSTANCE_NAME --zone ZONE
gcloud compute instances stop INSTANCE_NAME --zone ZONE
```

### Cloud Storage (gsutil)

**List buckets:**
```bash
gsutil ls
gsutil ls gs://bucket-name/
```

**List objects:**
```bash
gsutil ls gs://bucket-name/path/to/prefix/
gsutil ls -l gs://bucket-name/  # With details
```

**Copy files:**
```bash
gsutil cp local-file.txt gs://bucket-name/
gsutil cp gs://bucket-name/file.txt ./
gsutil cp -r gs://bucket-name/path/ ./local-dir/
```

**Sync directories:**
```bash
gsutil -m rsync -r ./local-dir gs://bucket-name/path/
gsutil -m rsync -r gs://bucket-name/path/ ./local-dir
```

**Get object metadata:**
```bash
gsutil stat gs://bucket-name/path/to/file.txt
```

### Cloud Logging

**List log names:**
```bash
gcloud logging logs list
```

**Read log entries:**
```bash
gcloud logging read "resource.type=cloud_run_revision" --limit 50 --format json
gcloud logging read "severity>=ERROR" --limit 100 --format="table(timestamp,severity,textPayload)"
```

**Tail logs (stream):**
```bash
gcloud logging tail "resource.type=cloud_run_revision" --format="value(timestamp,textPayload)"
```

**Filter by time:**
```bash
gcloud logging read "timestamp>=\"$(date -u -v-1H +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\"" --limit 100
# Linux: date -u -d '1 hour ago' +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ
```

### Cloud Run

**List services:**
```bash
gcloud run services list
gcloud run services list --region REGION
```

**Get service details:**
```bash
gcloud run services describe SERVICE_NAME --region REGION
```

**View logs:**
```bash
gcloud logging read "resource.type=cloud_run_revision AND resource.labels.service_name=SERVICE_NAME" --limit 50
```

### GKE (Kubernetes)

**List clusters:**
```bash
gcloud container clusters list
gcloud container clusters list --format="table(name,location,status)"
```

**Get credentials for kubectl:**
```bash
gcloud container clusters get-credentials CLUSTER_NAME --zone ZONE
gcloud container clusters get-credentials CLUSTER_NAME --region REGION
```

**Describe cluster:**
```bash
gcloud container clusters describe CLUSTER_NAME --zone ZONE
```

### IAM & Projects

**List projects:**
```bash
gcloud projects list
gcloud projects list --format="table(projectId,name)"
```

**Get current project:**
```bash
gcloud config get-value project
```

**List service accounts:**
```bash
gcloud iam service-accounts list
```

## Common Patterns

### Investigate Cloud Run Errors

```bash
# Step 1: List recent errors
gcloud logging read "resource.type=cloud_run_revision AND severity>=ERROR" --limit 20 --format="table(timestamp,textPayload)"

# Step 2: Tail logs for specific service
gcloud logging tail "resource.type=cloud_run_revision AND resource.labels.service_name=my-service"
```

### Find Recent Storage Objects

```bash
gsutil ls -l gs://bucket-name/ | sort -k2 -r | head -20
```

### Check Compute Instance Status

```bash
gcloud compute instances list --filter="status=RUNNING" --format="table(name,zone,machineType,status)"
```

## Advanced Options

### Output Formatting

```bash
# JSON
gcloud compute instances list --format=json

# Table
gcloud compute instances list --format="table(name,zone,status)"

# Custom fields
gcloud compute instances list --format="value(name,networkInterfaces[0].accessConfigs[0].natIP)"
```

### JQ Filtering

```bash
gcloud compute instances list --format=json | jq '.[] | {name, zone, status}'
gcloud logging read "severity>=ERROR" --limit 50 --format=json | jq '.entries[].textPayload'
```

## Examples

### ✅ Positive Pattern: Specify Project Explicitly

```bash
# ❌ BAD: May use wrong project
gcloud compute instances list

# ✅ GOOD: Specify project
gcloud compute instances list --project PROJECT_ID
# Or set default
gcloud config set project PROJECT_ID
```

### ✅ Positive Pattern: Use Filters Server-Side

```bash
# ❌ BAD: Fetch all then filter
gcloud compute instances list | grep RUNNING

# ✅ GOOD: Filter on server
gcloud compute instances list --filter="status=RUNNING"
```

## Troubleshooting

### Authentication Errors

```bash
gcloud auth list
gcloud auth application-default login
gcloud config get-value project
```

### Permission Denied

```bash
# Check current account
gcloud auth list

# Verify project access
gcloud projects describe PROJECT_ID
```

### Region/Zone Issues

```bash
gcloud config get-value compute/zone
gcloud config get-value compute/region
gcloud config set compute/zone ZONE
```

